00:29:31.470 --> 00:29:35.280
for themselves have to decipher one,
whether they were using

00:29:35.280 --> 00:29:36.820
one profile versus another.

00:29:36.820 --> 00:29:39.260
In some cases, that's not so easy.

00:29:39.370 --> 00:29:41.900
We leave the complexity on the
inside for us to figure out in

00:29:41.930 --> 00:29:44.100
terms of dividing the royalties.

00:29:44.160 --> 00:29:46.600
And then second,
we didn't want them to have to,

00:29:46.600 --> 00:29:48.110
as I said, come back for another license.

00:29:48.230 --> 00:29:53.720
We wanted this license to be evergreen
for any use of MPEG-4 Part 2.

00:29:53.820 --> 00:29:57.590
So it covers all those profiles,
and this happens to be the official

00:29:57.590 --> 00:30:02.910
reference to where those profiles
and this standard can be found.

00:30:03.320 --> 00:30:07.200
and not to confuse you anymore with that,
